==Sports and Recreation==
Carson City has never hosted any professional team sports. However, a variety of sports are offered a parks and recreation.&lt;ref name=&quot;CCRL&quot;&gt;{{cite web|url=http://www.carson-city.nv.us/Index.aspx?page=1248|title=Carson City Recreation|last=Staff Writer|date=5-14-2010|publisher=Carson City|accessdate=6-3-2010}}&lt;/ref&gt; Many neighborhood parks offers a wide variety of features, including picnic tables, beaches, restrooms, fishing, softball, basketball, pond, tennis, and volleyball. The largest park is the Mill park, which has a total of {{convert|51|acre|km2}} of land.&lt;ref&gt;{{cite web|url=http://www.carson-city.nv.us/Modules/ShowDocument.aspx?documentid=23413|title=Parks in Carson City|last=Staff Writer|publisher=Carson City|accessdate=6-3-2010}}&lt;/ref&gt;
While there are no ski slopes within Carson City, the city is located close to [[Heavenly Mountain Resort]], [[Diamond Peak (ski area)|Diamond Peak]] and [[Mt. Rose Ski Tahoe|Mount Rose]] skiing areas.&lt;ref&gt;{{cite web|url=http://maps.google.com/maps?oe=utf-8&amp;rls=org.mozilla:en-US:official&amp;client=firefox-a&amp;um=1&amp;ie=UTF-8&amp;q=Ski+resorts+near+Carson+City,+Nevada&amp;fb=1&amp;gl=us&amp;hq=Ski+resorts&amp;hnear=Carson+City,+NV&amp;view=text&amp;ei=tC4HTKGSHpPUM4H-wC0&amp;sa=X&amp;oi=local_group&amp;ct=more-results&amp;resnum=1&amp;ved=0CC8QtQMwAA|title=Ski resort near Carson Ctiy|author=Staff Writer|publisher=Google|accessdate=6-3-2010}}&lt;/ref&gt;

==Points of Interest==
''See also:'' [[National Register of Historic Places listings in Carson City, Nevada]]

===Museums===
*[[Nevada State Capitol]] – original capitol still housing the governor's offices with museum exhibits
*[[Nevada State Museum, Carson City|Nevada State Museum]] – former state mint featuring rock, mining and prehistoric exhibits, and a recreated [[Wild West]] village
*[[Nevada State Railroad Museum]] – featuring the [[Virginia and Truckee RR. Engines No. 18, The Dayton; and No. 22, The Inyo|Inyo]] locomotive and relocated Wabuska Railroad Station
*[[Stewart Indian School]] – museum collection includes items from former faculty, students and school&lt;ref&gt;http://www.nps.gov/nr/travel/nevada/ste.htm&lt;/ref&gt;
*Foreman-Roberts House Museum&lt;ref&gt;http://www.cchistorical.org/historicrobertshouse.htm&lt;/ref&gt; – Gothic Revival architecture, tours available.
*[[Sears-Ferris House]]&lt;ref&gt;http://nevadaculture.org/nsla/index.php?option=com_content&amp;task=view&amp;id=725&amp;Itemid=95&lt;/ref&gt; (not open to public) - home of [[George Washington Gale Ferris, Jr.|George Ferris]], inventor of the [[Ferris wheel]]
[[Image:Secret Beach - Lake Tahoe East Shore.jpg|thumb|right|200px|Secret Harbor Beach, Lake Tahoe]]

