* {{Cite encyclopedia
  | title = Clipper
  | encyclopedia = New International Encyclopaedia
  | volume = 5
  | pages = 39
  | publisher = Dodd Mead and Company
  | year = 1909
  | quote = Clipper ... probably connected with Dutch ''klepper'', fast horse
  | url =  http://books.google.com/books?id=qycVAAAAYAAJ&amp;dq=%22clipper%20ship%22&amp;lr=&amp;as_drrb_is=b&amp;as_minm_is=0&amp;as_miny_is=&amp;as_maxm_is=0&amp;as_maxy_is=&amp;num=100&amp;as_brr=4&amp;pg=PA39#v=onepage&amp;q=%22clipper%20ship%22&amp;f=false
  | accessdate = Mar. 6, 2010}}&lt;br /&gt;The above is incorrect. The Dutch word ''klepper'' does not mean fast horse. It means clatter, and was sometimes applied to a bell ringer.

